81
00:06:07,190 --> 00:06:11,800
♪Embracing the waves of the deep sea♪

82
00:06:13,120 --> 00:06:18,480
♪Paper kites aim for distant shores♪

83
00:06:18,480 --> 00:06:23,480
♪Tasting the delights of the world♪

84
00:06:23,510 --> 00:06:28,070
♪Years spread like painted umbrellas♪

85
00:06:28,220 --> 00:06:29,020
Master.

86
00:06:29,020 --> 00:06:30,620
♪Shielding the tiles from wind and rain♪

87
00:06:31,260 --> 00:06:32,780
Master, it hurts!

88
00:06:38,060 --> 00:06:39,820
Master, please! It hurts!

89
00:06:44,140 --> 00:06:45,940
Master!

90
00:06:48,940 --> 00:06:49,780
Is this right?

91
00:06:52,400 --> 00:06:57,480
♪Radiant as the night sky,
setting the city aflame♪

92
00:06:58,120 --> 00:07:00,810
♪Though trapped in deep mud,♪

93
00:07:01,040 --> 00:07:03,770
♪I fear no changes♪

94
00:07:04,100 --> 00:07:05,860
Here, your favorite candy.

95
00:07:05,860 --> 00:07:07,860
♪I intend on walking with you
till the end♪

96
00:07:08,910 --> 00:07:10,990
♪In the land of dreams,
I stay with you forever♪

97
00:07:11,180 --> 00:07:11,980
Your drawing is good.

98
00:07:14,020 --> 00:07:14,700
Give it to me.

99
00:07:14,700 --> 00:07:18,730
♪Let gossip and doubts dissolve
into the mist♪

100
00:07:23,740 --> 00:07:24,540
Master,

101
00:07:25,180 --> 00:07:26,540
my shoulders are swollen.

102
00:07:26,860 --> 00:07:28,420
I really can't keep up the training.

103
00:07:28,420 --> 00:07:30,380
You think earning your keep is easy?

104
00:07:30,460 --> 00:07:33,340
You can take breaks during training,

105
00:07:33,700 --> 00:07:35,020
but what about when you're on a mission?

106
00:07:35,580 --> 00:07:37,060
If you can't keep up,
it could cost your life.

107
00:07:38,300 --> 00:07:39,780
What you'll face in the future

108
00:07:39,940 --> 00:07:42,540
is far more dangerous
than you can imagine.

109
00:07:46,140 --> 00:07:47,100
How dangerous?

110
00:07:49,380 --> 00:07:50,180
Master,

111
00:07:50,940 --> 00:07:52,060
why not share

112
00:07:54,260 --> 00:07:55,740
some stories with me?

113
00:07:57,340 --> 00:07:58,340
Maybe

114
00:07:59,180 --> 00:08:00,460
hearing them

115
00:08:01,460 --> 00:08:02,940
will motivate me to continue training.

116
00:08:10,020 --> 00:08:11,420
You think I'm trying to scare you?

117
00:08:26,510 --> 00:08:32,270
♪A glance seals our fate♪

118
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:38,840
♪Without you, time fades into night♪

119
00:08:39,340 --> 00:08:41,060
You wanted to know
how dangerous it is, right?

120
00:08:41,700 --> 00:08:42,700
Take a good look.

121
00:08:46,660 --> 00:08:47,940
I'm lucky to be alive.

122
00:08:49,980 --> 00:08:50,980
Many people

123
00:08:52,740 --> 00:08:53,860
aren't so fortunate.

124
00:08:53,930 --> 00:08:54,810
♪Fate entwined♪

125
00:08:55,860 --> 00:08:58,080
♪Love and hatred intertwined♪

126
00:08:59,180 --> 00:09:01,040
♪My sorrow overwhelmed♪

127
00:09:01,260 --> 00:09:02,890
♪I gaze at the moon, longing for you♪

128
00:09:02,900 --> 00:09:04,420
Why did you choose to be an assassin?

129
00:09:05,820 --> 00:09:08,700
♪Love as vast as stars♪

130
00:09:09,580 --> 00:09:10,420
Like you,

131
00:09:11,820 --> 00:09:12,740
I'm an orphan.

132
00:09:13,700 --> 00:09:14,980
But you're running a workshop

133
00:09:15,460 --> 00:09:16,540
and can live a simple life.

134
00:09:18,100 --> 00:09:19,500
Why did you choose the hard way?

135
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:21,500
♪Without regrets♪

136
00:09:24,700 --> 00:09:26,060
Because I don't live for myself.

137
00:09:27,540 --> 00:09:28,940
I want her

138
00:09:29,540 --> 00:09:30,580
to have freedom and wealth.

139
00:09:31,020 --> 00:09:32,060
Once I've saved enough money,

140
00:09:32,700 --> 00:09:34,900
I plan to show her the world.

141
00:09:41,100 --> 00:09:42,740
The "her" you mentioned

142
00:09:43,740 --> 00:09:45,020
is your sister, huh?

143
00:09:47,220 --> 00:09:48,020
Master,

144
00:09:49,460 --> 00:09:52,380
can you treat me as well

145
00:09:53,260 --> 00:09:54,700
as you treat your sister?

146
00:09:56,440 --> 00:10:02,150
♪Secrets hidden
behind tear-stained marks♪

147
00:10:02,150 --> 00:10:03,100
♪Grant me a life
with no history replaying♪

148
00:10:03,100 --> 00:10:05,220
If you want to stay in the Gang

149
00:10:06,020 --> 00:10:08,180
and keep your life while making money,

150
00:10:08,780 --> 00:10:11,140
you better focus on your training.
Got it?

151
00:10:11,140 --> 00:10:15,720
♪All I ask is
to face the world anew with you♪

152
00:10:37,980 --> 00:10:38,740
Brother,

153
00:10:39,980 --> 00:10:41,580
my swing is worn out.

154
00:10:42,380 --> 00:10:44,220
It keeps creaking.

155
00:10:47,340 --> 00:10:48,700
It's not the problem of the swing.

156
00:10:49,460 --> 00:10:50,780
You're getting heavier.

157
00:10:51,980 --> 00:10:53,620
Look how tall you've grown.

158
00:10:54,220 --> 00:10:55,500
You used to be

159
00:10:56,220 --> 00:10:57,140
this tall.

160
00:11:00,140 --> 00:11:02,340
I used to carry you to the market.

161
00:11:03,860 --> 00:11:04,940
Now, I'm getting old.

162
00:11:05,500 --> 00:11:06,700
I probably can't carry you.

163
00:11:08,260 --> 00:11:09,060
Brother,

164
00:11:10,340 --> 00:11:11,820
it's been a long time
since you carried me.

165
00:11:14,180 --> 00:11:14,980
Yeah.

166
00:11:17,820 --> 00:11:19,860
It's been a long time
since I carried my sister.

167
00:11:20,620 --> 00:11:21,420
Come on.

168
00:11:27,580 --> 00:11:28,900
Here we go.

169
00:11:32,180 --> 00:11:34,380
You really have gotten a lot heavier.

170
00:11:35,540 --> 00:11:38,260
It's obviously because you've gotten older
and can't carry me anymore.

171
00:11:39,820 --> 00:11:41,100
Can't carry you?

172
00:11:41,660 --> 00:11:43,420
Let's see if I can't carry you or not.

173
00:11:50,380 --> 00:11:51,460
Brother,

174
00:11:52,340 --> 00:11:54,020
why are you so good to me?

175
00:11:55,140 --> 00:11:56,500
Because you're Mengchen.

176
00:12:03,820 --> 00:12:04,620
What's wrong?

177
00:12:06,860 --> 00:12:08,180
Does your shoulder hurt?

178
00:12:08,380 --> 00:12:09,180
It's alright.

179
00:12:10,220 --> 00:12:11,380
Why are you nervous?

180
00:12:14,300 --> 00:12:16,300
It's just that...

181
00:12:17,060 --> 00:12:18,900
we were so close just now.

182
00:12:19,620 --> 00:12:20,940
I got a bit nervous.

183
00:12:34,090 --> 00:12:38,160
